File: Over 4.5 million coronavirus tests have been completed. AFP/Douglas Magno JOHANNESBURG - The health department said 1,928 new COVID-19 cases were reported in the last 24 hours, bringing the total number to 702,131. South Africa's COVID-19 death toll has increased by 38. This brings the number of deaths in the country to 18,408. READ: 61 more COVID-19 deaths in SA Recoveries stand at 630,436 which translates to a recovery rate of 90 percent. This means the country has just over 53,287 active cases. Over 4.5 million coronavirus tests have been completed.